# 📚 Book Finder App

## 🌟 Overview
The **Book Finder App** is a lightweight and user-friendly React application that helps users discover books quickly.  
It connects to the **Open Library API** and allows searching by **book title** or **author name**.  

This project was built as part of a **Take-Home Challenge** to demonstrate the ability to interpret requirements, design solutions, and implement them effectively.

---

## 🚀 Features
- 🔍 Search for books by **title** or **author**  
- 🖼️ Display **book covers** (when available)  
- ✍️ Show **author names** and **publish year**  
- 📱 Responsive, mobile-friendly design  
- ⚡ Built with **React + Vite** for fast performance  
- 🎨 Styled using **Tailwind CSS**  
- 🛡️ Graceful error handling (e.g., when no results are found)  

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack
- **Framework**: React (with Vite)  
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS  
- **API**: Open Library API  
- **Deployment**: CodeSandbox  

---

## 📖 How to Use
1. Open the **Live Demo link** (provided below).  
2. Enter a **book title** or **author name** in the search bar.  
3. Click **Search**.  
4. Browse the results with cover image, title, author, and publish year.  

---

## 🔮 Future Enhancements
- Add **pagination** for large results.  
- Introduce a **loading spinner** while fetching data.  
- Enable search by **ISBN**.  
- Add **dark mode** support for better UX.  

